
---

# Scripts (with “IronCrypt” name)

Below are the scripts in `bin/`. Make sure to `chmod +x` them.

---

## bin/ironcrypt.sh (main menu / launcher)

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
# ironcrypt.sh - main launcher for IronCrypt

BASEDIR="$(cd "$(dirname "$0")" && pwd)"
clear
cat <<'BANNER'
=====================================
   IronCrypt — Recon CLI Tool
   Features: Port scan, Web enum
   Other options: Coming soon
=====================================
BANNER

PS3="Select an option (1-6): "
options=(
  "Port scan (nmap)"
  "Web enumeration (ffuf/gobuster)"
  "DDOS (coming soon)"
  "XSS automation (coming soon)"
  "Other (coming soon)"
  "Exit"
)

select opt in "${options[@]}"; do
  case "$REPLY" in
    1) "$BASEDIR/scan_ports.sh" ; break ;;
    2) "$BASEDIR/web_enum.sh" ; break ;;
    3) "$BASEDIR/ddos_stub.sh" ; break ;;
    4) "$BASEDIR/xss_stub.sh" ; break ;;
    5) "$BASEDIR/other_stub.sh" ; break ;;
    6) echo "Goodbye from IronCrypt." ; exit 0 ;;
    *) echo "Invalid option. Choose 1-6." ;;
  esac
done
